HEADWORD: Well-favored
<hw>Well"-fa"vored</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Handsome;
well-formed; beautiful; pleasing to the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rachel was beautiful and <qex>well-favored</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xxix. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wellhead</ent>⟦br⟧
